==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*swíxraz'', from Indo-European ''*su̯ékuro-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[swehur]] (German [[Schwager]]), Middle Dutch [[sweer]], Old Swedish [[svœr]], Gothic [[𐍃𐍅𐌰𐌹𐌷𐍂𐌰]].  The Indo-European root is also the source of Greek [[ἑκυρός]], Latin [[socer]], Old Russian [[свекръ]] (Russian [[свёкор]]).  Compare [[sweger|sweġer]].

